         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers0444">
               <p>Collins entered St John&apos;s College, <placeName>Cambridge</placeName> in <date
                     when="1771">1771</date>, receiving his <seg ana="degree">BA</seg> in <date
                     when="1776">1776</date> and <seg ana="degree">MA</seg> in <date when="1780"
                     >1780</date>. He was ordained deacon in <date when="1776">1776</date> and
                  assigned as a curate at <placeName>Rauceby</placeName> and <placeName>Cranwell,
                     Lincolnshire</placeName>, but dismissed for field preaching. He moved on to
                  curacies in <placeName>Hull</placeName> and under <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers0159.xml"/>John Berridge</persName> in
                     <placeName>Everton</placeName>, eventually persuading the Bishop of
                     <placeName>Chester</placeName> to ordain him a priest in <date when="1781"
                     >1781</date>. Meanwhile Collins had met <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>, and after ordination he
                  decided to remain in <seg ana="itinerancy">itinerant</seg> ministry, preaching for
                  both <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>&apos;s and Lady
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers0964.xml"/>Huntingdon</persName>&apos;s
                  connexions. His independence of approach led to a gradual cooling of his
                  relationship with <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>.
                  See <hi rend="italic">Alumni Catabrigienses</hi>; <hi rend="italic">DEB</hi> 242;
                  Stevenson, <hi rend="italic">City Road</hi>, 450–51; Vickers, <hi rend="italic"
                     >Dictionary</hi>, 74; and <hi rend="italic">WHS</hi> 9 (<date when="1913"
                     >1913</date>): 25–35, 49–58, 73–83.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
   </text>
